data.text:
Kenden Kirsch

Published 12:00 am Monday, September 8, 2008

Graveside services for Kenden Gregory Kirsch, 1 month and 10 days, of Ellendale, will be held at 2:30 p.m. Tuesday at the First Lutheran Cemetery in Ellendale. Friends and family are all welcome to come and celebrate Kenden’s life at that time.

Kenden died Saturday, Sept. 6, 2008, at St. Marys Hospital in Rochester.

Kenden Gregory Kirsch was born on July 27, 2008, at St. Marys Hospital in Rochester to Ashley Wayne and Brandon Kirsch. Kenden was baptized on Sept. 6, 2008, by the Rev. John Holt. Kenden was only with us for a short time but made a very lasting impression. He will always hold a special place in our hearts forever and we will have comfort knowing he is in a better place.

Those left to cherish his memory are his parents, Ashley Wayne and Brandon Kirsch; sister, Brooklyn Kirsch; grandparents, Greg and Holly Wayne, Tim and Julie Kirsch; uncles and aunts, Nicholas (Katie) Wayne, Nathan (Linnea) Wayne, Rochelle (Matt) McCune Joshua Kirsch and Tyler Meyer; cousins, Amelia Wayne, Alexa, Peyton and Cooper McCune; and many more relatives and friends.

Kenden was preceded in death by his twin brother, Hayden Timothy, on July 27, 2008; his great-grandparents; and an aunt, Jessica Stevens.
